<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1697,2012]" box="[151,1152,1697,1724]" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,633,1697,1724]" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">
3. 
<taxonomicName authority="Lesne, 1899" authorityName="Lesne" authorityYear="1899" box="[179,633,1697,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Bostrychoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megaceros">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[179,487,1697,1724]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">Bostrychoplites megaceros</emphasis>
Lesne, 1899
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Olivier, 1790)" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[688,1152,1697,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Bostrychoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornutus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[688,1152,1697,1724]" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[688,975,1697,1724]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">Bostrychoplites cornutus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier, A. G." box="[989,1144,1697,1723]" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" refId="ref2956" refString="Olivier, A. G. (1790) Encyclopedie methodique. Histoire naturelle. Insectes. Tome cinquieme. Chez Panckoucke, Imprimeur- Libraire, hotel de Thou, rue des Poitevins, Paris, 793 pp." type="book" year="1790">Olivier, 1790</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1697,2012]" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">
So far 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lesne" authorityYear="1899" box="[277,430,1734,1759]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Bostrychoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megaceros">
<emphasis box="[277,430,1734,1759]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">B. megaceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been only known its type specimen, namely a male collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1220,1321,1733,1759]" name="Tanzania" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
(Kondoa) (MNHN). After describing it (
<bibRefCitation author="Lesne, P." box="[486,636,1769,1796]" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" pagination="438 - 621" refId="ref2629" refString="Lesne, P. (1899 b) Revision des Coleopteres de la famille des Bostrychides. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 67, 438 - 621." type="journal article" year="1899">Lesne 1899b</bibRefCitation>
), Lesne never again addressed the species in his later diagnostic papers, and the only mention of the species was including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lesne" authorityYear="1899" box="[713,864,1806,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Bostrychoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megaceros">
<emphasis box="[713,864,1806,1831]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">B. megaceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Bostrichidae’s world catalogue (
<bibRefCitation author="Lesne, P." box="[1258,1393,1805,1831]" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" refId="ref2861" refString="Lesne, P. (1938) Bostrychidae. Coleopterorum Catalogus auspiciis et auxilio W. Junk editus a S. Schenkling. Pars 161. W. Junk, Berlin, 84 pp." type="book" year="1938">Lesne 1938</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lesne" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Bostrychoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megaceros">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">B. megaceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was also missing from the monograph of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Borowski &amp; Wegrzynowicz" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[762,904,1841,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Bostrichidae</taxonomicName>
of tropical Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Lesne, P." box="[1108,1241,1841,1867]" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" refId="ref2783" refString="Lesne, P. (1924) Les Coleopteres Bostrychides de l'Afrique Tropicale Francaise. Encyclopedie Entomologique. Vol. 3. Les Presses universitaires de France - Librairie Paul Lechevalier Paris, 301 pp." type="book" year="1924">Lesne 1924</bibRefCitation>
). Lesne described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lesne" authorityYear="1899" box="[151,303,1878,1903]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Bostrychoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megaceros">
<emphasis box="[151,303,1878,1903]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">B. megaceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly due to the size of the specimen and, consequently, more forward protruding outgrowths. The 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,1913,1939]" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">holotype</typeStatus>
is 
<quantity box="[282,361,1913,1940]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" unit="mm" value="18.0">18 mm</quantity>
long, while the maximum length of the related 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[894,1023,1914,1939]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Bostrychoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornutus">
<emphasis box="[894,1023,1914,1939]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">B. cornutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was supposed to be 
<quantity box="[1253,1353,1913,1940]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" unit="mm" value="17.5">17.5 mm</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lesne, P." pageId="1" pageNumber="591" pagination="438 - 621" refId="ref2629" refString="Lesne, P. (1899 b) Revision des Coleopteres de la famille des Bostrychides. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 67, 438 - 621." type="journal article" year="1899">Lesne 1899b</bibRefCitation>
). More pronounced morphological traits in larger specimens of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lesne" authorityYear="1899" box="[1062,1236,1949,1975]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Bostrychoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1062,1236,1949,1975]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">Bostrychoplites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are quite normal, particularly visible in its most frequently caught representative, namely 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[957,1086,1986,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Bostrychoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornutus">
<emphasis box="[957,1086,1986,2011]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">B. cornutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[199,327,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Bostrychoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornutus">
<emphasis box="[199,327,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">B. cornutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a very common species representing the Afrotropical distribution. It is a polyphagous species and can develop in the wood of various tree species occurring from semi-deserts to rainforests. The conditions for larvae development in such habitats are often extremely varied, hence the collections often have specimens of different body sizes. In an analysis of the material from many museums the body length of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[1091,1222,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Bostrychoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornutus">
<emphasis box="[1091,1222,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">B. cornutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found to vary from 
<quantity box="[213,346,295,321]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" unit="mm" value="12.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="6.0">6 to 18 mm</quantity>
, so some specimens can be even three times as large as the smallest ones. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lesne" authorityYear="1899" box="[1185,1351,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Bostrychoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maegaceros">
<emphasis box="[1185,1351,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">B. maegaceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is such an example of the upper limit size of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[572,701,331,356]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Bostrychoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornutus">
<emphasis box="[572,701,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">B. cornutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Full synonymy of the species names along with its geographical distribution is presented below.
</paragraph>
